OL,3,CStaff at yacht manufacturer facing
OL,4,C'temporary lay-off' due to operational
OL,5,Cissues
OL,7,FIn a statement, a spokesperson said:
OL,8,F"Following our statement last week, we
OL,9,Fwanted to give an update on
OL,10,Foperational issues which have delayed
OL,11,Four production schedule in December
OL,12,Fand regrettably, resulted in circa 100
OL,13,Fof our 2150 employees being placed on
OL,14,Fa temporary lay-off on 2 nd & 3 rd
OL,15,FJanuary 2025, with the option to take
OL,16,Fthis as paid holiday.
OL,18,F"We are working hard to rectify the
OL,19,Foperational issues, and we can now
OL,20,Fconfirm that the 100 staff will return
OL,21,Fby Monday 27th January.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
